The government’s pay-rise proposal for civil servants will shape not only Spain’s fiscal outlook but also the trajectory of its housing market. In an economy where stability itself has become a scarce commodity, the balance between purchasing power, fiscal discipline, and housing access may prove decisive for the country’s growth in the years ahead.

